<p>this prose is beige to the level of being on par with children's fiction, and not in a way that conceals or suggests cooler things behind it. things are what they are, no sentence demands further attention than its own contents. i feel like I could literally pick out any sentence and spin it into a more interesting sentence. maybe it's the writerly voice you have going on and it's dumb of me to try to change that, but I can't support a whole series written like this in any capacity.</p>

							</div>

								
					
